REMEMBER THIS: your wedding’s final to do is the wedding album. Then it’s truly complete. 

Why let your photographs just sit on your hard drive, or just be a part of your TikTok’s or some squares on Instagram? Print your memories to make them come to life. There’s truly nothing like seeing your wedding in print :)

For 2023/4 brides who inquire with us and book us within a week, we do something super special for them related to an album! 🤫 Mention this reel in your message to us!

When Sanya told me she wanted to always get a view of the baraat as it enters, we made sure it happened. 

Luckily @leonardspalazzo555 has their bridal suites situated such that she was able to sneak in a view of Moazzam entering on the horse 🐎. 

Such cute and precious moments!
A 50lb wedding dress! 🥹🫠😅

❗️IMP WEDDING TIP -SAVE FOR LATER❗️ If you’re planning to use smoke grenades for your grand entrance, make sure they
1) last super long so at least 1 minute 
2) are vivid in colour 
3) are ALWAYS behind you. People holding the smoke grenades should NOT enter beside you or in front of you. 

It may sound so simple, but I can’t emphasize #2 enough! The number of times we’ve had to yell mid-entrances for people to stay behind is crazy. If the smoke is in front of you, there’s going to be nothing but a photo of a white sheet 😅

Totally get the Sabyasachi hype now 🫠🥹🥰

❗️Food station ideas for your wedding, especially mehendi/henna night ❗️

We often talk to couples were always worried that their guests might not have a lot of fun at their events because they might be “boring”. While that’s not true, because everyone really enjoys themselves at weddings, one way you can add on a different, entertaining dimension to your events would be by adding food stations. 

One such idea would be to add on a Kulfi stand along with your desserts! Something like this actually does really well at events like Mehendi’s. :) 

This particular vendor is @kulfihut_ in the GTA. Their kulfis are delicious! My favourite is the pistachio and mango 🤤

🔊 READ IF YOU’RE GOING TO HAVE SPARKULARS AT YOUR EVENT! 

If you are planning to have sparkulars at your event, make sure that you are budgeting enough time for your photographer to take your photos with them. Often times couples schedule a portion in their itinerary BEFORE the guests enter the hall to take some photos with them, rather than waiting when everyone is in the hall and it’s crowded. If you plan on using them for photos after you enter and during your event, make sure you talk to your vendor about keeping them on for at least a minute! Sometimes great photos take some time to happen, so give you a photographer they are desired time to get those beautiful bright shots with the sparkulars.

If you book your dream car - MAKE SURE YOU GET PHOTOS WITH IT! 

Discuss it with your photographer, and come up with locations that can actually help them take photos with your car. Often times many locations do not provide a nice enough backdrop for a car to be parked while taking photos.  Consider the location, parking situation, the crowd situation, and most importantly, the spot where you would park the car without disruption to take pictures!
